.TH "dpm_suspend_start" 9 "dpm_suspend_start" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dpm_suspend_start \- Prepare devices for PM transition and suspend them.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" dpm_suspend_start
.BI "(pm_message_t state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "state" 12
PM transition of the system being carried out.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Prepare all non-sysdev devices for system PM transition and execute "suspend"
callbacks for them.
